# Task 3:
1. Create an anacron job which executes a script with echo Hello > /opt/hello and runs every 2 days

[student@localhost chapter5]$ vi hello.sh
#!/bin/bash

echo "Hello" > /opt/hello

[student@localhost chapter5]$ sudo vi /etc/anacrontab
#period in days   delay in minutes   job-identifier   command
1       5       cron.daily              nice run-parts /etc/cron.daily
7       25      cron.weekly             nice run-parts /etc/cron.weekly
@monthly 45     cron.monthly            nice run-parts /etc/cron.monthly
2       0       anacron.hello   /home/student/chapter5/hello.sh

2. Create a cron job which executes the same command (will be better to create a script for this) and runs it in 1 minute after system boot.

[student@localhost ~]$ sudo crontab -u root -e
no crontab for root - using an empty one
crontab: installing new crontab
[student@localhost ~]$ sudo crontab -u root -l
@reboot sleep 60; /home/student/chapter5/hello.sh

[student@localhost chapter5]$ sudo shutdown -r now

3. Restart your virtual machine and check previous job proper execution

[student@localhost ~]$ ls /opt
[student@localhost ~]$ ls /opt
hello
